node.text:
This couple said, "See you later, alligator!" to single life as they married in the same place where they fell in love just 8 years earlier. 🐊"Charles and I met in college at the #UniversityOfFlorida," recalls @sorevawaslike. "We were both covering the Florida gymnastics team...me for the school radio station and him for the newspaper.” 📻📰
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Sports had played a special role in the couple's relationship, so it was only fitting that they weaved it into the fabric of their wedding day. 🏈 From a first look inside the university’s football stadium to walking down the aisle surrounded by blue and orange pom poms, Reva and Charles included fun "I Do" details (think custom Jordans and a Gator cake 👟) inspired by their alma mater. 🧡💍

node.text: “I tried on about 80 dresses before heading to #Kleinfeld to find my @RandyFenoli gown,” @SarahMerrill_Hall tells @BRIDES. 👰🏼‍♀️“The type of dress that I thought I wanted turned out to be the style that I liked the least. 💭 So I was very surprised by what I fell in love with! 🥰 It’s a lot like dating — sometimes you think you know what you want, and other times, the one that isn’t exactly your type catches you by surprise.” ✨l @BigKidProblems #Kleinfeld

It was the afternoon of Nani and Robert's 8th grade graduation, which marked the day the two would head to different high schools. 🎓 @NonDan remembers, "Robert, who just got his braces off, wanted me to see his new smile! 😃 So he ran across the football field to tell me I looked pretty in my dress and to show me that he got his braces off." 🏃
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Fast forward some years, an unexpected MySpace message had brought Nani and Robert together again. 💻 "Robert asked if I wanted to go out with him and some friends. 💌 He picked me up the following weekend and we have been together ever since. Meeting my best friend at such a young age has been an absolute privilege — I can’t wait to see where life takes us!” 👩‍❤️‍👨
